FBIS4-20224 "drweu082__a94021" FBIS-WEU-94-082-A Daily Report 28 April 1994 ANNEX Italy & Vatican City Scalfaro To Be `Attentive, Insistent' on Employment Scalfaro To Be `Attentive, Insistent' on Employment BR2804111394 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1057 GMT 28 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR2804111394 Rome ANSAMAIL Database English BFN [Unattributed article: "Scalfaro To Be `Insistent' on Employment"] [Text] (ANSA) Cagliari, April 28 -- President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro said he would be "attentive and insistent" on employment issues during the term of the government expected to be ushered in by his meeting at 5 p.m. (1500 GMT) this afternoon with the leader of the conservative coalition that won the elections, media magnate Silvio Berlusconi. Talking to reporters at the inauguration of the Cagliari Fair, Scalfaro was asked if Berlusconi's word would be enough to allay conflict of interest concerns. "I cannot say before we have had a talk," was his reply.
